Please maintain social distancing guidelines and wear a mask. All attendees are encouraged to bring their own chair to make social distancing easier to accomplish. Only substitutes need to attend the meeting; please do not bring anyone else.

ATTENTION ALL LASALLE PARISH STUDENTS AND PARENTS:

Due to the Governor's mandate for all schools in Louisiana to remain closed for the 2019-2020 school year, LaSalle Parish schools will continue providing all students with educational packets to be completed at home.

Each individual school will provide information about packet distribution for their students for the remaining 4 weeks of school. Parents are required to return their students' packet as instructed by their school. Each school is providing packet information via automated J-calls, the school's website and/or the school's Facebook page.

Information concerning student promotion will be provided in the near future as the guidelines are released by the Louisiana Department of Education.

Thank you and stay safe.

5. Please pass this information along to any other substitutes that you are in contact with.

GOV. EDWARDS' NEW ORDER: (3/23/2020)

In response to Gov. Edwards’ stay-at-home order, LaSalle Parish Schools will not be offering grab-and-go meals as of March 24, 2020. We will continue to monitor the issue and will let you know if we can resume the program.

We want to service our students but we also have to consider the safety and well-being of our faculty, staff and their families. The safety of our students and employees must remain our top priority.

We as a community must do our part to keep everyone safe from COVID-19.

post_text:
MARCH 20 ANNOUNCEMENT: INFORMATION REGARDING MEALS FOR STUDENTS

The LaSalle Parish School System would like to extend our appreciation to parents and community members for their cooperation in our efforts to continue to educate our children.

Beginning Monday, March 23, we will be providing bagged breakfast and lunch for our students. The locations will be at Jena Elementary and Olla Elementary between the hours 10:00-11:00 a.m. Monday through Friday.

We ask that everyone remain in their vehicle and proceed through the drive-thru lines as directed. We will hand out as many as 5 lunches per vehicle. If more is needed for that car, they will have to go to the end of the line until all others have received their bags.

Meals will be handed out by faculty and staff that have volunteered to come hand out the bags. Again, no one will be allowed outside of their vehicle. Please be respectful and take only the number of meals for your children. This will continue for a 3-week period ending Thursday, April 9th.

post_text:
MARCH 16 UPDATE: Beginning Thursday, March 19th, two feeding sites will serve breakfast and lunch to allow school-aged children to continue receiving nutritious meals each weekday.

Parents will be able to drive up to Jena Elementary School OR Olla Elementary School for meals during designated times.

Teachers are also creating lessons for students to complete while schools are closed. Parents/Guardians will be contacted by schools with specific information.

As you all know, this situation is rapidly evolving and changing. Our goal is to do the best we can for our students during this time. Public education is the backbone of our society and is the only place many of our children receive any sort of educational instruction and in many cases the only meals they have. If we all work together, we can make the best of this time and still be there for our students.

Please be patient as we work through this process together.

post_text:
Pursuant to BESE Bulletin 1566, students seeking to transfer to a public school in grades 5 or 9 from any

• In-state nonpublic school,
• Approved home study program, or
• Out-of-state school,

shall be required to pass the English language arts and mathematics portions of the state placement test.

This test is a computer-based test that is designed to measure students’ knowledge and skills in ELA and math pursuant to Louisiana Student Standards in grades 4 and 8. The test is consistent with the LEAP 2025 test. Both ELA and Math have three sessions.

Tests will be administered August 6 & 7 at Jena High School. To register your child for the state placement test, contact the LaSalle Parish Special Education Office at 992-5971 by 12:00 p.m. August 3.

post_text:
The LaSalle Parish School Board requirements for each substitute employee:

Applications will be available each Tuesday from 1:00-4:00 p.m. only. At this time, applications may be picked up and complete application packets may be returned. Incomplete packets will not be accepted.
Provide a copy of your high school diploma, transcript, certificate, and, if applicable, verification of college hours or your university transcript(s). A copy of your driver's license and social security card are also required.
Upon return of the complete packet, applicants will be scheduled for background checks at the LaSalle Parish Sheriff's Office, where you will be required to pay $15.
Once the background results are returned to the School Board Office, you will be added to the substitute list and the school(s) at which you would like to sub will be notified.

LaSalle Parish Schools added 15 new photos — at LaSalle Parish Schools.
June 18, 2013 at 7:19 PM · Jena, LA ·

Jenene Bignar, Speech Language Pathologist from the LaSalle Parish Schools Special Education Department, presented an inservice on "Tasks Galore." Special Education personnel who work with children with significant disabilities were provided with LETA Boxes designed by Jenene. These educators were very excited to be provided with an overview of how to use these boxes and how to design their own. They were also trained on how to use picture schedules, visual charts, SymbolStix, and Unique. Afterwards, these educators were allowed to make their own materials to use in the upcoming school year. Attending the workshop were Dennis Harris, Meg Falgoust, Kayla Elmore, Tabatha Cooper, Chasity Sherrill, Jenene Bignar, and Ethel Smith, Special Education Supervisor.

ACT Prep Sessions...
Jena High School will host ACT Prep Sessions for any high school student who is planning to take the ACT.

The sessions will take place on each Wednesday immediately following school in Room 113. Sessions will last from 3:30 to 5:30 p.m.

Students needing assistance to prepare for the ACT are urged to take advantage of this great opportunity! The tutoring sessions will continue through mid-April, and are facilitated by certified teachers.

For more information, contact the school at 992-5195.

post_text:
Jena High School hosts after-school tutoring for high school students on Tuesdays and Thursdays of each week. The tutoring is held in Room 102 from 3:30 to 5:30 p.m.

Students needing assistance with school work or to prepare for the ACT are urged to take advantage of this opportunity. Students should bring their materials for which they need tutoring.

The tutoring will continue for the duration of the school year, and is facilitated by certified teachers.

For more information, contact the school at 992-5195.
